{
  "texts": [
    "Understanding ViTs has increasingly relied on layer-wise analysis, echoing early findings in language models where information about individual tokens is lost and later recovered across depth (Voita et al., 2019).",
    "In vision, this perspective has highlighted two key points.",
    "First, positional encodings (PEs) dominate early representations, causing shallow layers to emphasize spatial location over semantic content (Amir et al., 2021).",
    "Our work interprets the addition of PEs as a functionally critical decorrelation event (the \"Cliff\" in Cliff-Plateau-Climb) in our experiments.",
    "Second, the conventional role of the [CLS] token as a global information aggregator (Dosovitskiy et al., 2020) is increasingly questioned."
  ]
}